		<div id="comment_body_64483635"><p>In the cloud, you do not have backups, you have redundancies. But if you delete stuff in part a, it will get replicated to part b and c of the datacenter. Depending on how much you pay you may or may not get some local (as in not at the same datacenter) or buy it twice to get geographical redundancies.</p></div>
	</div>

